   derived around 300 concepts (visualization techniques, mining
   techniques, and analysis tasks) and built a taxonomy for each type of
   concept. The co-occurrence relationships between the concepts were also
   extracted. Our research can be used as a stepping-stone for other
   researchers to 1) understand a common set of concepts used in this
   research topic; 2) facilitate the exploration of the relationships
   between visualization techniques, mining techniques, and analysis tasks;
   3) understand the current practice in developing visual text analytics
   tools; 4) seek potential research opportunities by narrowing the gulf
   between visualization and mining techniques based on the analysis tasks;
