Abstract = {{Nonnegative Matrix Factorization (NMF) and Concept Factorization (CF)
   are two popular methods for finding the low-rank approximation of
   nonnegative matrix. Different from NMF, CF can be applied not only to
   the matrix containing negative values but also to the kernel space.
