   Matrix Factorization (GNMF) and Locally Consistent Clustering
   Factorization (LCCF) can significandy improve the performance of
   clustering. Unfortunately, these are unsupervised learning methods. In
   order to enhance the clustering performance with the supervisory
   information, a Semi-Supervised Concept Factorization (SSCF) is proposed
   in this paper by incorporating the pairwise constraints into CF as the
   reward and penalty terms, which can guarantee that the data points
   belonging to a cluster in the original space are still in the same
   cluster in the transformed space. By comparing with the
   state-of-the-arts algorithms (KM, NMF, CF, LCCF, GNMF, PCCF),
