Abstract = {{Topic modeling methods like LSI, pLSI, and LDA have been widely studied
   in text mining domain for various applications like document
   representation, document clustering/classification, information
   retrieval, etc. However, such unsupervised methods are effective over
   corpus with well separable topics. In real-world applications, topics
   might be of highly overlapping in nature. For example, a news corpus of
   different terror attacks has highly overlapping keywords across
   reporting of different terror events. In this paper, we propose a
   variant of LDA, named as Prioritized Named Entity driven LDA (PNE-LDA),
