Abstract = {{A feature word vector based on short text clustering algorithm is
   proposed in this paper to solve the poor clustering of short text caused
   by sparse feature and quick updates of short text. Firstly, the formula
   for feature word extraction based on word part-of-speech (POS) weighting
   is defined and used to extract a feature word as short text. Secondly,
   the word vector that represents the semantics of the feature word was
   obtained through training in large-scale corpus with the Continuous
   Skip-gram Model. Finally, Word Mover's Distance (WMD) was used to
   calculate similarity of short texts for short text clustering in the
   hierarchical clustering algorithm. The evaluation of four testing
   datasets revealed that the proposed algorithm is significantly superior
   to traditional clustering algorithms, with a mean F value of 55.43\% on
