Abstract = {{Usually, clustering algorithms consider that document collections are
   static and are processed as a whole. However, in contexts where data is
   constantly being produced (e.g. the Web), systems that receive and
   process documents incrementally are becoming more and more important. We
   propose OHDOCLUS, an online and hierarchical algorithm for document
   clustering. OHDOCLUS creates a tree of clusters where documents are
   classified as soon as they are received. It is based on COBWEB and
   CLASSIT, two well-known data clustering algorithms that create
   hierarchies of probabilistic concepts and were seldom applied to text
   data. An experimental evaluation was conducted with categorized corpora,
