   However, most of the current algorithms need to predefine a clustering
   number, which is difficult to obtain. Moreover, the mutli-label
   clustering is useful in multiple clustering tasks in many applications,
   but related works are rarely available. Although several studies have
   attempted to solve above two problems, there is a need for methods that
   can solve the two issues simultaneously. Therefore, we propose a new
   text clustering algorithm called Word2Cluster. Word2Cluster can
   automatically generate an adaptive number of clusters and support
   multi-label clustering. To test the performance of Wrod2Cluster, we
   build a Chinese text dataset, Hotline, according to real world
   applications. To evaluate the clustering results better, we propose an
   improved evaluation method based on basic accuracy, precision and recall
   for multi-label text clustering. Experimental results on a Chinese text
