Abstract = {{Network-based document clustering involves forming clusters of documents
   based on their significance and relationship strength. This approach can
   be used with various types of metadata that express the significance of
   the documents and the relationships among them. In this study, we
   defined a probabilistic network graph for fine-grained document
   clustering and developed a probabilistic generative model and
   calculation method. Furthermore, a novel neural-network-based network
   embedding learning method was devised that considers the significance of
   a document based on its rankings with external measures, such as the
   download counts of relevant files, and reflects the relationship
   strength between the documents. By considering the significance of a
   document, reputative documents of clusters can be centralized and shown
   as representative documents for tasks such as data analysis and data
   representation. During evaluation tests, the proposed ranking-based
   network-embedding method performs significantly better on various
   algorithms, such as the k-means algorithm and common word/phrase-based
