   better scene understanding. In this paper we address the problem of
   scene text retrieval: given a text query, the system must return all
   images containing the queried text. The novelty of the proposed model
   consists in the usage of a single shot CNN architecture that predicts at
   the same time bounding boxes and a compact text representation of the
   words in them. In this way, the text based image retrieval task can be
   casted as a simple nearest neighbor search of the query text
   representation over the outputs of the CNN over the entire image
