Abstract = {{Traditional statistical retrieval models often treat each document as a
   whole. In many cases, however, a document is relevant to a query only
   because a small part of it contain the targeted information. In this
   work, we propose a neural passage model (NPM) that uses passage-level
   information to improve the performance of ad-hoc retrieval. Instead of
   using a single window to extract passages, our model automatically
   learns to weight passages with different granularities in the training
